HEADWORD: Dishallow
<hw>Dis*hal"low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make unholy;
to profane.</def> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor can the unholiness of the priest <qex>dishallow</qex> the
altar.</q> <rj><qau>T. Adams.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disharmonious</ent>⟦br⟧
